<br>
I have never quad kited. ok I said it <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  Now where would be a good place to learn? I am one yellow shy of DING'ing to level 52. Could someone please give me a nOOBie type guild for getting 51 - 55 quading somewhere? zones? mobs? <br>
<br>
Thank you for any help &amp; information you can provide!<br>
<br>
Nizadar Ravensrath<br>
Channeler of the 51st level<br>
&lt;Iron Cross&gt;<br>
Tarew Marr <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=cova69>Cova69</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(7/12/01 7:49:51 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Going to teach myself the *art of quading* !</span><hr size=1> I can't help much with suggestions of what to kill in that lvl range, as I'm not yet there myself (4<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/glasses.gif ALT="8)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> , though I'm planning on doing the wyverns in CS as soon as I get the mana and spells to do so (should be 51).<br>
<br>
As for the &quot;art of quadding&quot; though, I'd suggest going to EW and practicing on the walruses/ulthorks.  Ya, they'll be way green.  But quadding is something you really wanna know how the mobs generally react when ya do stuff, and have a bit of experience with rounding them up, snaring, judging range (flux staff), etc.  And ya may get some decent loot (tusks) while you're there learning.<br>
<br>
Once ya learn how it works, you'll find it to be one of the most useful solo tactics there is - not even just for exp.  Quadding greens to pharm loot/for faction is something I find myself doing more and more often, and it's a lot more efficient than using DD's. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uwandork.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Wandor K</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(7/12/01 12:07:34 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Going to teach myself the *art of quading* !</span><hr size=1> I agree 100%, practice on greens first. Only difference is I would precatice on the drakkel wolves in GD. This should help your dorf/CoV faction if you are not already friendly with these groups. CoV faction is important becasue it will make quading wyverns in CS MUCH easier. I am amiable to CoV so I dont hvae to worry about pulling down to the beach, drakes, named, or people dragging chests/sirens/bulthars on the beach. Plus you can bank/buy/sell in SS.<br>
<br>
Once you have it down, try the wyverns. Start with only 2-3 per pull until you get used to the wyverns. Be sure to pull with a flux staff, otherwise you will get too many resists. If you don't have a flux staff, go get one. You can do the quest in about 2 hrs (I redid this quest last night - long story) and this will make quading MUCH easier. <p><span style="font-size: 14px; font-famliy: arial"><b>Wandor Kilbringer<br>Channeler of the 52nd Conclave<br>Vini, Vidi, Nuki</b></span><br>
<i>I came, I saw, I nuked the crap out of everything in sight!</i><p>
<span style="font-size: 14px; font-famliy: arial"><b>Moordian Killbringer<br>Warrior of 26 Battle Scars</b><br><i>Dwarven LaMachine of Death</i><br><span style="font-size: 12px; font-famliy: arial">proud member of Infinity Watch - Terris-Thule server</span></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/utegellan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tegellan</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(7/18/01 5:30:15 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Going to teach myself the *art of quading* !</span><hr size=1>  Do what Wandor said until level 53 (that was the level I started to be able to quad raptors with good chances of success), then go to the raptors and blast through the levels. Or even better group, quadding is amazing exp but I will take a group with my friends any day of the week <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
